post_text:
Doing School Safely through COVID

Brinkley Family, we are excited for our students to return to school on Monday!!! Students and families make our school community the caring place that it is. However, in order for us to have a successful school year we need your help with the following things:

‚Ä¢ Keeping your child at home if he or she has a fever of 100.4 and/or are sick or experiencing cough, chills, shortness of breath, difficulty breathing or loss of taste or smell
‚Ä¢ Notifying the school if your child has been exposed to someone with COVID-19
‚Ä¢ Making sure your child wears a face mask to school daily
‚Ä¢ Modeling for them how to stand 6ft apart
‚Ä¢ Demonstrating how to wash and sanitize hands
‚Ä¢ Calling before coming to the school
‚Ä¢ Not escorting students inside the building

Thank you for your assistance. Together we can keep our Brinkley School District family safe, healthy, and ready to learn during this unique time.

post_text:
As part of our on-going effort to transform the culture of Brinkley School District, we applied and have been awarded the grant to become a part of the Opportunity Culture initiative. We are excited about joining a national initiative of over 360 schools across the country, resulting in students receiving excellent instruction from teacher leaders and their teams. The Opportunity Culture Initiative will allow our District to:

1. Reach more students with excellent teachers and their teams
2. Pay teachers more for extending their reach
3. Fund pay within regular budgets
4. Provide protected in-school time and clarity about how to use it for planning, collaboration, and development
5. Match authority and accountability to each person‚Äôs responsibilities

post_text: Notice: Brinkley Public Schools will be pausing athletics, temporarily. This pause of Athletics includes Football practice and Basketball practice. The reason for the temporary pause is because we have had a student athlete come in contact with a person at their place of employment that tested positive for the Covid-19 virus. We will be deep cleaning and treating the practice areas and locker rooms. Coaches and Student athletes will be getting tested to see if they may have contracted the virus. Brinkley Public Schools will always strive to follow all guidelines giving to us by Arkansas Department of Health, the Governor, and other qualified entities. We will always do our best to be transparent with the parents, students, school faculty, district employees, and community. If you have any questions, you may contact the Superintendent‚Äôs office at 870-734-5105 or by our social media sites Facebook and Twitter, Thank you.

post_text:
Brinkley Parents and Guardians,

Thank you for replying to our school reentry survey. We are compiling responses from our various stakeholder groups, and the committee is actively working to develop a reentry plan. Once the plan is complete, it will be sent to the board of directors for final approval. The goal is to have the plan published in mid-July and posted to the district website. Additionally, the key components that directly impact you will be published in the newspaper and all social media platforms. We will schedule an onsite meeting date and time for specific grade levels to come to the school and complete registration and pick up a hard copy of the School Reentry Plan. Any questions you have can be addressed on your scheduled onsite day. Social distance guidelines will be posted on the campus. Masks will be required.

post_text:
Notice: We have formed a reentry to school committee and we are working to develop guidelines for the re-opening of school in August. With guidance from the Arkansas Division of Elementary and Secondary Education, which will largely mandate our direction, having your feedback is crucial to our ability to respond and direct resources and support appropriately.
We have developed a survey to gather information on how to best meet your needs and to understand your concerns regarding the potential upcoming return to school in August. This anonymous survey should take less than ten minutes to complete. The survey is located on the internet at www.brinkleyschools.com, on our Brinkley School app which is available for download to any mobile android device or apple device. The survey is available as well on social media platforms Facebook and twitter, and will also be attached to the accompanying text message with this call out. If you have any questions about the survey or reentry in general please call us at 870-734-5000.

Survey Link: https://bit.ly/2VblWvE

05.09.2005 -the day Signature Bank of Arkansas was born. We are so proud to have spent the last 15 years serving our communities, and can't wait to see what the next 15 bring. Until we can gather together, we're making our anniversary celebration a day of gratitude to those who are keeping our communities fed.

Join us in saluting 15 incredible organizations working hard to keep students and families across NWA and Brinkley fed:
Ability Tree

Springdale School District
Tri Cycle Farms

post_text:
Words cannot express how grateful I am for the Brinkley School District staff!!! It has been an awesome week of hard work. The bus drivers and para professionals went out this morning to deliver AMI packets and some snacks for our students. The cafeteria workers prepared breakfast and lunches for the students all week, the transportation supervisor delivered the food, the social worker assisted in all departments, the teachers created AMI packets, the administrators planned meetings and organized schedules and AMI distribution, the secretaries answered the phones, made copies, and assisted staff, the central office staff kept the District afloat, the custodians and maintanence staff kept the buildings sanitized and the grounds and facilities maintained! Despite everything that is going on, we are continuing to meet the needs of our students, while practicing social distance.

‚ÄúGreat things in business are never done by one person, they are done by a team of people.‚Äù Steve Job

#TigerStrongüêÖüêÖ

Dear Parents and Guardians:

Governor Hutchinson has closed schools through April 17. When the Department of Education provides us with further information, I will release the next steps.

The most important thing is to make sure you and your child(ren), stay healthy.

Please make sure to have your child complete the AMI packets. After spring break, I will post a date for them to be returned to the school. The packets must be completed for your child to receive grades and attendance credit.

As always, the Brinkley School District administrators and staff stand ready to assist you.

Remember, ‚ÄúTough times never last, but tough people do.‚Äù ~Robert H Schuller

March‚Äôs Spotlight on Excellence is Mrs. Regina Parker, Mrs. Marsha Hamner, and Ms. Sandra Glasgow. These ladies go above and beyond for the students and staff and do it with a lot of heart. They exemplify what it means to be a part of a team, uphold the values of the District, and are committed way beyond the hours they are paid for. Please join the Brinkley School District in celebrating these three team members.

School Choice Notification:

Please be advised that the Arkansas Public School Choice Act of 2015 dictates that a district can lose 3% of its students in one year. The Brinkley School District has met that percentage as of January 27, 2020. However, if that percentage changes, the public will be notified, and additional applications will be accepted. Under section 2-3.01 of the School Choice Act, if a student seeks to attend a school in a nonresident district, the student‚Äôs parent shall submit an application to the nonresident district with a copy to the student‚Äôs resident district.
( 2-3.01.1).

Dear Parents and Guardians,

You and your child are invited to a special event.
Guest speakers will discuss the various opportunities available for students that may have an interest or a passion to learn more about educational pathways to join the outdoor industry. This summit will provide information about scholarships, grant programs and career opportunities that are available now. During this event, students will be encouraged and educated on the different youth programs in the area, traditional and non-traditional ways to qualify for job opportunities in wildlife conservation, agriculture, gaming, and fishing arenas. The Ivory Billed Hunting Lodge is also excited to offer young hunting enthusiast a free hunt with a paying adult.

The summit is free and open to the public.
Date: Saturday, December 14, 2019 Time: 11:00am-1:00pm Location: Brinkley Convention Center, Brinkley, AR

There will be door prizes and free food!!!

For more information please contact Ivory Billed Hunting Lodge Team at:
ivorybilledlodge@gmail.com or call 615-806-3021

(Brinkley High School and C.B. Partee are working with the Division of Elementary & Secondary Education to implement a framework developed by Marzano Research called High-Reliability Schools. As part of this process, we are collecting feedback from parents, students, and staff through an online survey administered by the Hanover Research firm. Survey responses will be anonymous and data will only be reported as a group.
You will see two questions in this survey that ask whether you are a European Union citizen or are currently located in the European Union (EU). Hanover Research is required to ask these questions to comply with the General Data Protection Regulation, a new EU policy that gives citizens and others traveling in the EU greater control over their personal data.
The survey should take less than 10 minutes to complete. To begin, please click the following link:

https://bit.ly/2pqsfyn

Thank you for your time and participation!
shared_text:
